Formula	Explanation
tr:nth-of-type(n)	Selects all table rows.
tr:nth-of-type(n+2)	Selects all table rows except
the first row (starting with the second row).
tr:nth-of-type(2n)	Selects every second row of the table.
tr:nth-of-type(3n)	Selects every third row of the table.
tr:nth-of-type(2n+4)	Selects every other row of the table,
starting with the fourth row.
td:nth-of-type(2)	Selects the second column.
td:nth-of-type(2n)	Selects every second column of the table.
td:nth-of-type(-n+3)	Selects first three columns of the table.

each even row (tbody tr:nth-of-type(even))
each odd row (tbody tr:nth-of-type(odd))
all columns starting with the second column (tbody td:nth-of-type(n+2))
the last row and column (tbody tr:last-of-type, tbody td:last-of-type)
the second last row (tbody tr:nth-last-of-type(2))
the table data inside the last 3 rows (tbody tr:nth-last-of-type(-n+3) td)
adding a hover effect to all rows in the tbody section (tbody tr:hover)

tbody tr:nth-of-type(even){
 background-color: #F3F3F3;
}

tbody tr:nth-of-type(odd) {
 background-color:#ddd;
}

tbody td:nth-of-type(n+2){
 text-align: right;
}

tbody tr:last-of-type,  tbody td:last-of-type {
 font-weight: bold;
 font-size:1.25em;
}


tbody tr:nth-last-of-type(2){
 color: red;
}

tbody tr:nth-last-of-type(-n+3) td{
 text-align: right;
}

tbody tr:hover 
{
 cursor:pointer;
 background-color: #808080;
 color: #dadada;
}
